eter-kafka-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENFL's%3C%2Fa%3E%20preeminent%20player%20evaluation%2C%20it%20revealed%20that%20I%20have%20several%20skills%20that%20pro%20teams%20are%20looking%20for.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20outperformed%20nearly%20all%20draft%20prospects%20in%20certain%20categories%20of%20this%20test%2C%20floundering%20on%20only%20one.%20The%20best%20part%3F%20I%20didn't%20even%20break%20a%20sweat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20the%20exam%20while%20sitting%20in%20an%20office%20chair%20within%20the%20suburban%20Tennessee%20corporate%20headquarters%20of%20a%20testing%20startup%20called%20S2%20Cognition.%20Purporting%20to%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%20sports%20evaluation%20that%20scientifically%20measures%20an%20athlete's%20game-speed%20cognitive%20abilities%20down%20to%20a%20millisecond%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20these%20tests%20%E2%80%94%20which%20feel%20like%20a%20cross%20between%20playing%20Pong%20and%20taking%20an%20eye%20exam%20%E2%80%94%20have%20fast%20become%20part%20and%20parcel%20of%20how%20many%20scouts%20find%20the%20next%20billion-dollar%20athlete.%20More%20than%2052%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessors-turned-porn-stars-free-speech-campus-battle-wisconsin-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolleges%20and%20universities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2016%20of%20the%20NFL's%2032%20teams%20pay%20S2%20to%20administer%20tests%20to%20prospective%20signees%20and%20to%20keep%20the%20results%20confidential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJack%20Marucci%2C%20the%20longtime%20athletic-training%20director%20at%20the%20SEC%20powerhouse%20Louisiana%20State%20University%2C%20told%20me%20the%20tests%20helped%20him%20identify%20his%20athletes'%20natural%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%20and%20adjust%20their%20training%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20them.%20%26quot%3BWe%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20Maseratis%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Marucci%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20we've%20got%20to%20fine-tune%20the%20engine%20a%20little%20bit%20and%20find%20out%20what's%20going%20to%20make%20them%20stay%20at%20that%20high%20gear.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20others%20have%20questioned%20S2's%20professed%20efficacy%2C%20the%20company%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Equickly%20expanding%20beyond%20sports%20and%20into%20law%20enforcement%2C%20the%20military%2C%20and%20even%20the%20boardroom.%20In%20the%20not-distant%20future%2C%20as%20the%20corporate%20hiring%20process%20grows%20ever%20more%20layered%20and%20as%20the%20compulsion%20to%20measure%20every%20conceivable%20facet%20of%20ourselves%20grows%20ever%20more%20feverish%2C%20you%20might%20be%20taking%20a%20version%20of%20this%20high-speed%2C%20highly%20stressful%20test%20to%20land%20your%20next%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20brought%20me%20to%20Nashville.%20I%20may%20be%20genetically%20damned%20to%20never%20be%20a%20Tennessee%20Titan%2C%20but%20perhaps%20my%20test%20results%20can%20help%20propel%20me%20to%20become%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-tech-industry-fire-managers-ceo-hire-coders-developers-executives-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etitan%20of%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Somehow%2C%20I%20have%20a%20slightly%20easier%20time%20believing%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%20at%20S2's%20brand-new%2C%20still%20undecorated%20offices%20this%20spring%2C%20I%20was%20greeted%20by%20its%20founders%2C%20Brandon%20Ally%20and%20Scott%20Wylie%2C%20two%20college%20athletes%20turned%20neuroscientists.%20After%20spending%20their%20early%20careers%20researching%20individual%20differences%20in%20cognitive%20deterioration%20%E2%80%94%20Ally%20studied%20Alzheimer's%20disease%20and%20Wylie%20studied%20Parkinson's%20disease%20%E2%80%94%20they%20founded%20S2%20in%202015%2C%20deciding%20they%20could%20apply%20their%20work%20to%20studying%20individual%20differences%20in%20cognitive%20function%20in%20world-class%20athletes.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20essentially%20working%20at%20both%20ends%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20from%20breakdown%20to%20elite%20expression%20of%20cognitive%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20Ally%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20drew%20interest%20for%20their%20work%20with%20quarterbacks%2C%20who%20often%20need%20to%20be%20the%20quickest%20thinkers%20on%20the%20football%20field.%20The%20difference%20between%20throwing%20a%20touchdown%20and%20taking%20a%20brutal%20sack%20could%20be%20that%20extra%20tenth%20of%20a%20second%20the%20QB%20takes%20to%20see%20patterns%20developing%20downfield.%20To%20gauge%20whether%20a%20QB%20has%20the%20brainpower%20to%20handle%20the%20pressure%20and%20noise%2C%20S2%20has%20designed%20a%20sequence%20of%20tests%20to%20measure%20their%20reaction%20time%2C%20impulse%20control%2C%20and%20processing%20speed%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eamong%20other%20traits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202016%2C%20S2%20had%20found%20a%20hungry%20market%20in%20the%20NFL.%20For%20general%20managers%2C%20drafting%20and%20trading%20players%20are%20high-stakes%20decisions%2C%20with%20up%20to%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20managers'%20own%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20line.%20Selecting%20the%20wrong%20quarterback%20can%20set%20a%20franchise%20back%20years%2C%20while%20nabbing%20the%20next%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatrick-mahomes-defends-dad-bod-great-body-quarterback-nfl-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPatrick%20Mahomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Lamar%20Jackson%20(neither%20of%20whom%20was%20the%20first%20quarterback%20drafted%20in%20his%20class)%20can%20catapult%20a%20team%20to%20year-after-year%20Super%20Bowl%20contention.%20Small%20wonder%20teams%20would%20pay%20a%20king's%20ransom%20for%20a%20test%20that%20promises%20to%20give%20them%20an%20edge%20in%20knowing%20which%20quarterback%20to%20draft%20out%20of%20college%20or%20sign%20in%20free%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20years%2C%20the%20standard-bearer%20for%20evaluating%20the%20brains%20of%20NFL%20athletes%20was%20the%20Wonderlic%2C%20a%20short%20IQ%20test%20with%20a%20series%20of%20increasingly%20difficult%20questions.%20While%20the%20test%20is%20still%20used%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20often%20as%20part%20of%20the%20interview%20process%2C%20it%20has%20largely%20fallen%20out%20of%20favor%20in%20pro%20sports%20as%20research%20has%20indicated%20its%20scores%20are%20not%20statistically%20correlated%20with%20athletic%20performance.%20The%20Wonderlic%20has%20also%20been%20criticized%20as%20perpetuating%20racial%20and%20socioeconomic%20biases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20always%20living%20under%20the%20ghost%20of%20the%20Wonderlic%2C%26quot%3B%20Ally%20says.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20think%20whatever's%20between%20the%20ears%20is%20all%20sort%20of%20the%20same%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it's%20all%20IQ.%26quot%3B%20For%20S2%2C%20he%20says%2C%20it's%20a%20marketing%20challenge%20as%20much%20as%20anything%20to%20convince%20prospective%20clients%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%20things%20in%20the%20brain%2C%20and%20that%20the%20brain%20does%2C%20that%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20correlate%20to%20performance%20in%20sports.%26quot%3B%20John%20Michel%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organizations%20at%20Loyola%20University%20Maryland%20who%20has%20extensively%20studied%20the%20efficacy%20of%20testing%20in%20workplaces%2C%20agrees%20there's%20a%20distinction.%20While%20the%20Wonderlic%2C%20he%20says%2C%20assesses%20only%20crystallized%20intelligence%20(%26quot%3BHow%20well%20can%20you%20remember%20something%20you've%20learned%3F%26quot%3B)%2C%20the%20S2%20gauges%20fluid%20intelligence%20(%26quot%3BHow%20well%20can%20you%20observe%20multiple%20objects%20moving%20at%20once%20in%20space%3F%20How%20well%20can%20you%20keep%20track%20of%20things%3F%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20everyone%20is%20convinced%20that%20S2%20is%20a%20magic%20bullet.%20In%20April%202023%2C%20an%20independent%20reporter%20published%20leaked%20test%20results%20from%20the%20Ohio%20State%20quarterback%20C.J.%20Stroud%2C%20then%20favored%20to%20be%20the%20first%20player%20selected%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-draft-first-round-quarterbacks-busts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENFL%20draft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20over%20the%20Alabama%20quarterback%20Bryce%20Young.%20The%20report%20indicated%20that%20Stroud%20had%20bombed%20the%20S2%2C%20scoring%20in%20the%2018th%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epercentile%2C%20while%20Young%20scored%20in%20the%2098th.%20One%20week%20later%2C%20Young%20was%20drafted%20first%20overall%2C%20and%20Stroud%20fell%20to%20second.%20But%20then%20Stroud%2C%20the%20alleged%20dolt%2C%20went%20on%20to%20have%20one%20of%20the%20best%20rookie%20campaigns%20of%20any%20NFL%20quarterback%2C%20while%20Young%20struggled%20all%20year.%20Headlines%20flooded%20in%20calling%20the%20S2%20the%20second%20coming%20of%20the%20Wonderlic%2C%20or%20an%20outright%20sham.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20S2%20won't%20publicly%20talk%20about%20the%20details%20of%20Stroud's%20results%2C%20Ally%20said%20Stroud's%20reported%20score%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20legit.%26quot%3B%20Stroud%20himself%20seemed%20to%20admit%20he%20didn't%20give%20the%20test%20his%20full%20effort%3A%20%26quot%3BSome%20things%20I%20apply%20myself%20to%2C%20some%20things%20I%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20The%20Athletic%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20backlash%20has%20continued%20into%20this%20year.%20In%20February%2C%20the%20prominent%20sports%20agency%20Athletes%20First%2C%20which%20represents%20Stroud%2C%20the%20Jets%20quarterback%20Aaron%20Rodgers%2C%20and%20many%20other%20top%20players%2C%20instructed%20its%20clients%20to%20skip%20cognitive%20evaluations%20including%20the%20S2%20and%20Athletic%20Intelligence%20Quotient%2C%20a%20rival%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20S2%20office%2C%20it%20was%20time%20for%20me%20to%20take%20the%20test.%20Unlike%20the%20Wonderlic%2C%20the%20S2%20isn't%20anything%20like%20a%20standardized%20exam%3A%20It's%20a%20rapid-fire%20battery%20of%20pressure-filled%20visual%20simulations%20that%20require%20split-second%20decision-making%2C%20conducted%20on%20a%20gaming%20laptop%20or%20Xbox%20console%20connected%20to%20a%20hypersensitive%20keypad.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%20if%20you%20have%20Einsteinian-level%20IQ%20or%20you%20barely%20pulled%20a%20D-minus%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20Wylie%20told%20me%20just%20before%20I%20began.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20going%20to%20help%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20agreed%20I%20wouldn't%20divulge%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20test%2C%20but%20I'll%20say%20that%20there%20are%20eight%20five-minute%20modules%3A%20One%20evaluates%20your%20perception%20speed%2C%20another%20your%20tracking%20ability%2C%20and%20another%20your%20abilities%20to%20intuit%20a%20pattern%20on%20the%20fly.%20Many%20of%20them%20involve%20dots%20flying%20around%20a%20screen%20or%20flashing%20before%20your%20eyes%2C%20and%20demand%20an%20instant%20reactions%20by%20clicking%20a%20button%20or%20pressing%20an%20arrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20grueling%2C%20requiring%20intense%20concentration%20and%20locked-in%20vision.%20I%20wasn't%20on%20a%20football%20field%20with%20300-pound%20linemen%20protecting%20me%20from%20shifty%20edge%20rushers%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20the%20pressure.%20There%20were%20moments%20when%20I%20felt%20completely%20in%20the%20zone%2C%20and%20others%20when%20some%20subconscious%20impulse%20led%20my%20button-mashing%20prowess%20astray.%20By%20the%20end%20I%20felt%20exhausted%2C%20and%20I%20was%20certain%20I'd%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EUnfazed%20by%20the%20controversy%20over%20Stroud%2C%20S2%20has%20begun%20selling%20its%20tests%20to%20other%20sectors.%20The%20several%20law-enforcement%20agencies%20and%20special%20operations%20military%20groups%20it%20has%20partnered%20with%20so%20far%20feel%20like%20a%20natural%20extension%3A%20People%20in%20both%20fields%20often%20require%20the%20same%20high-pressure%2C%20split-second%20decision-making%20skills%20as%20athletes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20company's%20expansion%20into%20corporate%20settings%20is%20a%20more%20significant%20departure.%20Can%20a%20test%20originally%20designed%20for%20pass%20rushers%20and%20designated%20hitters%20really%20help%20companies%2C%20as%20S2%20claims%20it%20can%2C%20evaluate%20outside%20talent%2C%20invest%20in%20worker%20training%2C%20and%20fast-track%20potential%20executives%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20metrics-intensive%20corporations%2C%20S2's%20testing%20isn't%20all%20that%20different%20from%20what%20they've%20been%20using%20to%20assess%20candidates%20for%20decades.%20IQ%20tests%20and%20personality%20tests%20like%20the%20Myers-Briggs%20or%20the%20Enneagram%20have%20long%20been%20deployed%20to%20evaluate%20candidates'%20aptitude%2C%20intelligence%2C%20and%20cultural%20fit.%20Many%20of%20the%20world's%20top%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20Boeing%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Alphabet%2C%20already%20do%20many%20of%20the%20things%20S2%20is%20offering%2C%20albeit%20by%20compiling%20teams%20of%20psychometricians%20or%20human-resources%20experts%20in%20bespoke%20assessment%20centers.%20It's%20no%20surprise%2C%20then%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-hates-workday-human-resources-customer-service-software-fortune-500-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFortune%20500%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20reaching%20out%20to%20S2.%20(The%20company%20won't%20disclose%20its%20nonathletic%20clients.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20field%20goal%20post%20with%20a%20bar%20graph%20being%20hit%20with%20a%20football%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6679a0aad1c84a0eaca72744%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%20if%20you%20have%20Einsteinian-level%20IQ%20or%20you%20barely%20pulled%20a%20D-minus%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20S2%20cofounder%20Scott%20Wylie.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20going%20to%20help%20you%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20S2.%3Cp%3EAlberto%20Miranda%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20S2%20ran%20a%20pilot%20program%20at%20three%20companies%20in%20different%20industries.%20Wylie%20says%20it%20focused%20on%20evaluating%20employees%20and%20discussing%20with%20them%2C%20rather%20than%20their%20managers%2C%20how%20their%20results%20could%20help%20them%20%26quot%3Bunderstand%20themselves%20a%20little%20bit%20better%20beyond%20just%20personality%20and%20group%20dynamics%26quot%3B%20and%20find%20ways%20to%20adjust%20their%20workflows%20or%20different%20roles%20they%20could%20move%20to.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20help%20every%20individual%20maximize%20their%20performance%20and%20efficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20Wylie%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bgosh%2C%20that's%20just%20going%20to%20elevate%20departments%2C%20elevate%20teams.%26quot%3B%20The%20S2%20team%20learned%20that%20some%20workers%20were%20more%20sensitive%20than%20others%20about%20what%20they%20wanted%20their%20employers%20to%20know%20about%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ally%20and%20Wylie%20evaluate%20so-called%20corporate%20athletes%20%E2%80%94%20a%20term%20that%20makes%20even%20them%20cringe%20a%20bit%2C%20though%20they%20nevertheless%20use%20%E2%80%94%20they%20look%20at%20dynamic%20memory%20systems%2C%20including%20explicit%20and%20implicit%20memory%20(think%20recall%20versus%20intuition)%2C%20and%20executive%20cognitive%20systems%20(such%20as%20impulse%20control%20and%20risk-taking).%20Some%20of%20these%20have%20crossover%20with%20a%20pro%20athlete's%20skill%20set%2C%20while%20others%20fall%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichel%20says%20a%20fluid-intelligence%20test%20like%20the%20S2%20could%20be%20helpful%20in%20deciding%20whether%20a%20candidate%20would%20make%20the%20right%20hire%20or%20whether%20an%20employee%20is%20right%20for%20a%20managerial%20role%2C%20but%20only%20as%20part%20of%20a%20suite%20of%20tests%20and%20reviews%20of%20their%20work%20product%2C%20or%20as%20a%20way%20to%20narrow%20down%20a%20large%20pool%20of%20interview%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWylie%20and%20Ally%20also%20say%20their%20tests%20should%20work%20in%20tandem%20with%20other%20evaluations.%20After%20all%2C%20perhaps%20there's%20no%20bigger%20red%20flag%20for%20a%20prospective%20employee%20than%20when%20your%20future%20employer%20relies%20on%20one%20metric%20to%20say%20whether%20you're%20a%20fit%20or%20not%2C%20whether%20you%20can%20handle%20the%20work%20and%20live%20up%20to%20expectations.%20I%20know%20I'd%20be%20turned%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20finishing%20my%20test%2C%20I%20nervously%20trudged%20down%20the%20hall%20to%20a%20conference%20room%2C%20where%20Wylie%20had%20my%20results%20displayed%20on%20a%20laptop%20screen.%20To%20my%20surprise%2C%20he%20was%20smiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turned%20out%20that%20my%20tracking%20capacity%20%E2%80%94%20my%20ability%20to%20follow%20movements%20around%20a%20screen%20%E2%80%94%20was%20less%20than%20stellar.%20Among%20NFL%20prospects%2C%20I%20would%20have%20scored%20in%20the%206th%20percentile.%20My%20perception%20speed%20was%20fairly%20average%20(48th)%20and%20my%20impulse%20control%20above%20average%20(84th).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20instinctive%20learning%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20I%20had%20to%20trust%20my%20gut%2C%20figure%20out%20a%20pattern%2C%20and%20stick%20with%20it%20despite%20distractions%20being%20thrown%20my%20way%20%E2%80%94%20I%20somehow%20scored%20in%20the%2097th%20percentile.%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20get%20up%20and%20say%2C%20oh%20man%2C%20that%20was%20tough%2C%26quot%3B%20Wylie%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20actually%20deduced%20the%20optimal%20responses%20very%20quickly%2C%20very%20efficiently.%20A%20lot%20of%20our%20general%20managers%20crush%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20I%20had%20told%20Wylie%20that%20I%20was%20easily%20distractible%20and%20often%20struggled%20to%20focus.%20But%20then%20I%20scored%20in%20the%2098th%20percentile%20on%20the%20distraction-control%20test.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%20what%20you%20say%3A%20When%20you%20want%20to%20lock%20in%20and%20block%20out%20distractions%2C%20you%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Wylie%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%2C%20it's%20time%20for%20me%2C%20as%20a%20worker%2C%20to%20amend%20my%20environment%20so%20I%20can%20find%20better%20ways%20to%20remove%20distractions%20and%20lock%20in.%20When%20I%20finally%20do%20that%2C%20NFL%20front%20offices%20should%20give%20me%20a%20call.%20I%20won't%20need%20the%20tracking%20ability%20of%20an%20NFL%20safety%20watching%20a%20play%20unfold%20in%20front%20of%20him%2C%20but%20maybe%20I%20can%20run%20a%20franchise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fscott-nover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScott%20Nover%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20writer%20based%20in%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio.%20He%20is%20a%20contributing%20writer%20at%20Slate%20and%20was%20previously%20a%20staff%20writer%20at%20Quartz%20and%20Adweek%20covering%20media%20and%20technology.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-job-stress-test-nfl-football-ceo-careers-s2-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719482281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6679a04e40cf2af6e4f512d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-job-stress-test-nfl-football-ceo-careers-s2-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Quarterbacks%20take%20this%20test%20to%20get%20into%20the%20NFL.%20You%20might%20have%20to%20take%20it%20to%20get%20your%20next%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Scott%20Nover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-job-stress-test-nfl-football-ceo-careers-s2-2024-6%22%2C%2