bhead%20in%20a%202024%20article%20by%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20advised%2C%20as%20it%20urged%20readers%20and%20economies%20to%20pivot%20away%20from%20their%20dependency%20on%20non-renewable%20sources%20of%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20article%20beckoned%20countries%20to%20take%20notes%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20successful%20tryst%20with%20clean%20energy%2C%20it%20reasoned%20why.%20%E2%80%9CSince%202015%2C%20India%20has%20connected%2028%20million%20households%2C%20impacting%20120%20million%20people%2C%20to%20the%20electricity%20grids%20%E2%80%94%20a%20third%20of%20the%20global%20total%20during%20the%20last%20decade.%20In%20this%20duration%2C%20the%20country%20has%20also%20added%20more%20than%201%2C50%2C000%20MW%20of%20clean%20energy%20capacity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20article%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20solar%20power%20being%20given%20a%20warm%20welcome%20from%20sectors%20ranging%20from%20education%20and%20healthcare%20to%20farming%20and%20small%20businesses%2C%20the%20country%20is%20seeing%20a%20profound%20shift%20in%20the%20way%20businesses%20are%20evolving%20to%20meet%20their%20energy%20requirements.%20And%20the%20statistics%20are%20telling.%20As%20the%20Global%20Electricity%20Review%202024%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20growth%20in%20solar%20generation%20in%202023%20pushed%20the%20country%20past%20Japan%20to%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20third-largest%20solar%20power%20generator.%20It%20has%20climbed%20from%20ranking%20ninth%20in%202015.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20is%20in%20clear%20sight%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20to%20achieve%20500%20GW%20of%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20by%202030.%20But%20as%20the%20energy%20transition%20is%20underway%20and%20industries%20hustle%20to%20do%20their%20bit%20to%20go%20solar%2C%20there%20are%20success%20stories%20emerging%20from%20pockets%20across%20India%20where%20households%2C%20farming%20entrepreneurs%2C%20and%20street%20vendors%20are%20championing%20a%20similar%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5C